item.dc:creator: @vernorexia vernorexia
item.description:
@vernorexia wrote:

malimt:

i had this problem with no-ip but then i found out that i didnt portforward properly … so it didnt connect and also it could be possible ur brother is running (utorrent, bittorrent, or any torrent downloader application… ) … try it again try portforwarding it again

finally some common sense, its nothing to do with no-ip like he said you just have to portforward properly, to check your port go to canyouseeme.org

item.title: Error Connecting To Server
item.dc:creator: @vernorexia vernorexia
item.description:
@vernorexia wrote:

[quote=“anti man444, post:14, topic:473130”][quote author=sk8rdude461 link=topic=591029.msg4180525#msg4180525 date=1355463667]

ok well i changed the ip in client.java (client sided) to my no-ip and when my bro trys to connect it says error connecting :l

There no need to do that though, no-ip does work, only reason it wouldn’t is port forwarded wrong

If your brother is using your wireless/internet… he needs to log on using the 127.0.0.1 not your no-ip.

Lol what?
127.0.0.1 is LOCALHOST. Meaning the ONE MACHINE only…

Host just needs to port forward correctly.

yeah… he isnt connected to it though… hes connected through his no-ip… so his brother should try the localhost to see if it works.

DUDE are you serious right now?
His brother will NOT be able to connect to the server that is ON A DIFFERENT COMPUTER through localhost. LOCAL HOST IS LOCAL.
Computer A is the server.
Computer B is his brother.
If B trys connecting to A with localhost. NOTHING will work. UNDERSTAND?
[/quote]

why you guys making it so hard?
and why you would use no-ip?
some server are not working with no-ip for some reason…
just use this ip: http://whatismyipaddress.com/
that ip you need to insert in
client.java

(may sure you need only change in client.java cause some server have also applet_sub.java and there you need also to change the ip!)

if you will be sure just go to src then push on ctrl+f (search) than type 127.0.0.1 so you can see in which files you need to change ;)[/quote]
